This was a delicious dish! Made it for brunch with a few changes. Due to not having an ovenproof skillet, I just sauteed the garlic and onions, then the bell pepper and broccoli rabe. I mixed the rest of the ingredients and just poured it in the pan. Turned it on low and flipped it once it was really set. Great recipe, everyone loved it - definitely added to my recipe book!

Rating: 4
This was absolutely delicious and tasted even better room temperature as leftovers for lunch the next day. The key to making sure this doesn't taste bland is to make sure that you go to a cheese shop or specialty market and get really good, aged Italian-style provolone. A lot of what is sold as "provolone" at your average chain supermarket is bland and rubbery and bears no resemblance to real provolone.

