Rating: 3
I made this for a women's book club brunch along with a ham and cheese strata. This frittata was devoured eagerly and even those who claimed not to like broccoli rabe enjoyed it. It came out like something you could get in a restaurant - most impressive for not much work. The dish also stood well - I made it about two hours before we ate it, let it cool, then rewarmed right before eating.

Rating: 4
I made this tonight, it was great. I used sharp cheddar since we didn't have provolone but otherwise made it as directed. I really liked the oregano, it gave it an interesting flavor, and the sweet onions & peppers balanced the bitter rabe really well. This one is a crowd-pleaser (just make sure the crowd likes broccoli rabe, some people really dislike it).

